5 Commands You’ll Use Daily

1. ps
- Shows running processes
Example:
ps aux

2. top
- Real-time system monitoring
- Shows CPU, memory usage

3. htop (better version of top)
- Interactive and easier to read

4. systemctl
- Manage services

Examples:

- systemctl status nginx
- systemctl restart nginx

5. journalctl
- View system logs

Example:

journalctl -u nginx


🔹 Linux Man Pages

- Instead of memorizing, learn how to read docs.

Examples:
- man ps
- man top
- man systemctl

What you get:

- Command usage
- Options
- Examples

-----------

🔹 systemd 
- Controls services in Linux
- Handles startup, shutdown, restarts

Common workflow:
- systemctl status nginx
- systemctl restart nginx
- journalctl -u nginx

If something breaks → you check:

- Status
- Logs
- Restart service
